<span class="doc-tag">.q2w-share</span>
<h1 class="doc-h1">Share</h1>
<p class="doc-lead">Copyable map URL, current-view metadata, and share action for collaborative WebGIS workflows.</p>

<section class="doc-section">
  <h2>Preview</h2>
  <div class="doc-preview" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #eef2f7, #dbe3ec); height: 260px;">
    <div class="q2w-share q2w-share--floating" style="width:420px;">
      <div class="q2w-share__head">
        <div>
          <div class="q2w-share__title">Share current map view</div>
          <div class="q2w-share__meta">Zoom 13 · Cirebon Land Value · 4 layers visible</div>
        </div>
        <span class="q2w-share__badge">Live URL</span>
      </div>
      <div class="q2w-share__field">
        <code data-doc-share-url>https://q2w-mapcss.pages.dev/examples/categorized-real/#13/-6.7797/108.4714</code>
        <button class="q2w-btn q2w-btn--primary q2w-btn--sm" data-doc-share-copy>Copy link</button>
      </div>
      <div class="q2w-share__actions">
        <button class="q2w-btn q2w-btn--ghost q2w-btn--sm">Embed</button>
        <button class="q2w-btn q2w-btn--ghost q2w-btn--sm">Open preview</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="doc-section">
  <h2>Usage</h2>
  <div class="doc-code"><button class="doc-copy">copy</button><pre>&lt;div class="q2w-share q2w-share--floating"&gt;
  &lt;div class="q2w-share__head"&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;
      &lt;div class="q2w-share__title"&gt;Share current map view&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class="q2w-share__meta"&gt;Zoom 13 · 4 layers visible&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;span class="q2w-share__badge"&gt;Live URL&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="q2w-share__field"&gt;
    &lt;code&gt;https://example.com/map/#13/-6.7797/108.4714&lt;/code&gt;
    &lt;button class="q2w-btn q2w-btn--primary q2w-btn--sm"&gt;Copy link&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</pre></div>
</section>

<section class="doc-section">
  <h2>Behavior</h2>
  <p>The framework styles the share UI. Your app can update the URL from Leaflet state using <code>map.getCenter()</code>, <code>map.getZoom()</code>, or a hash plugin. The docs preview demonstrates copy feedback.</p>
</section>

